%I A066242 #23 Jul 21 2026 10:24:13
%S A066242 2,18,20,32,45,63
%N A066242 floor(log(x)^2)-perfect numbers, where f-perfect numbers for an arithmetical function f are defined in A066218.
%H A066242 Joseph L. Pe, <a href="https://vixra.org/abs/2503.0165">On a Generalization of Perfect Numbers</a>, J. Rec. Math. 31:3 (2002), 168-172.
%e A066242 Let f(x) = floor(log(x)^2). Then f(18) = 8 = 4+3+1+0+0 = f(9)+f(6)+f(3)f(2)+f(1); so 18 is a term of the sequence.
%t A066242 f[x_ ] := Floor[Log[x]^2]; Select[ Range[2, 10^5], 2 * f[ # ] == Apply[ Plus, Map[ f, Divisors[ # ] ] ] & ]
%Y A066242 Cf. A066218.
%K A066242 nonn,more,changed
%O A066242 1,1
%A A066242 _Joseph L. Pe_, Dec 19 2001
